This paper deals with learning semantic parsers, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses using dynamic programming and crowdsourcing, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with filtering out spurious logical forms, which is a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
